  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "cc @kubernetes/sig-node\r\npid cgroup https://www.kernel.org/doc/Documentation/cgroup-v1/pids.txt allows limiting the number of processes per cgroup, and very critical to avoid fork bombs. docker seems to have added support since 1.11 release: docker/docker#18697\r\n\r\nI can think of two options to expose this in k8s api:\r\n1. Add it to pod.spec.container.resources.limit  as a container resource limit: pids-limit, or\r\n2. Expose it as a PodSecurityPolicy securityContext which gets applied to all pods at admission. ",
